    <note>Xiang(2) Zonghui [17297] Eldest surviving son, treated as son #1 and younger brother, Zongliang [17298], as son #2 of Jing [3351]. He was accused, stripped of his noble titles and transported to Binzhou (Hunan) in ca. 1102, therefore, I assume purged by Cai(1) Jing's [1649] clique, whereas his brother Zongliang was accused of being tight with Cai(1) Jing by Chen(1) Guan [7128] and also purged. CBD, 1, 635.</note>
